.TH QDMISSING 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-qdtools" "SmartMet Tools"
.SH NAME
qdmissing \- report missing values in querydata
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B qdmissing
.RI [ options ]
.I querydata
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B qdmissing
prints how much of the given querydata is missing, expressed by default
as a percentage. The output may be aggregated globally, per time step,
or per station, and the program can also be used as a guard in scripts
that should fail when too much data is missing.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h
Print the help message.
.TP
.B \-n
Count NaN values instead of computing a missing-value percentage.
.TP
.B \-N
Print the count instead of the percentage.
.TP
.B \-t
Analyse all time steps separately.
.TP
.B \-w
Analyse all stations separately.
.TP
.BI \-e " limit"
Exit with a non-zero status when more than
.I limit
values are missing.
.TP
.BI \-T " zone"
Time zone to use when printing time stamps.
.TP
.BI \-P " param1,param2,..."
The parameters to inspect.
.TP
.B \-Z
Suppress rows whose value is zero.
.SH EXAMPLES
Per-time-step report for temperature:
.PP
.RS 4
qdmissing \-t \-P Temperature forecast.sqd
.RE
.PP
Fail if more than 5% of values are missing:
.PP
.RS 4
qdmissing \-e 5 forecast.sqd
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR qdstat (1),
.BR qdcheck (1),
.BR qdinfo (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
.PP
